    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-04-05T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-04-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="191"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d191">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 738.3915/56</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">American Minister</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-04-05">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 5, 1911</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Pending final decision of the boundary controversy, the Haitian Government
                    refuses to consent to continuance of work on Pedernales road.</p>
                <p>The Department is informed by the minister of Haiti that he has received from his
                    Government full powers to negotiate with the Dominican Government a protocol for
                    arbitration, and he requests the Department to endeavor to have similar
                    authorization given to the Dominican minister in Washington, in order that the
                    submission of the boundary controversy to arbitration may be promptly concluded.
                    This Government would be glad, as has heretofore been stated, to assist in
                    framing a protocol of arbitration.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">P. C. Knox.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
